Stir your hands with warm or cold running water.
Current water is recommended because containers with stagnant water can be contaminated, while the temperature of the water appears to make no difference.
Fleet your hands to form foam with a generous amount of soap, including the backs of your hands, between your fingers and under your nails.
The soap removes the germs from the skin, and studies indicate that people usually wash their hands more thoroughly when using soap than when using water alone.
